-- Tamweel, Amlak Customers Move Loans to DIB, Mashreqbank, National Reports
-- Arif Sharif
-- 2010-06-21T04:32:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/tamweel-amlak-customers-move-loans-to-dib-mashreqbank-national-reports.html

          
          
             Tamweel PJSC and Amlak Finance PJSC
home mortgage customers are moving their loans to other banks as
the two companies work on a planned merger,  The National 
reported, citing a mortgage industry official.  
 Dubai Islamic Bank PJSC and Mashreqbank PSC have begun
taking over some of the mortgages from Tamweel and Amlak, the
newspaper said, citing Kimberly Warren, the regional head of
mortgage advisory  John Charcol . Both companies told customers
they will not need to pay early redemption charges if they had
their loans refinanced by other banks, the National said.  
